         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="0012_002414_000286_0001.jpg" xml:id="d4e39"/>
            <p>Messrs. Charles Pettit &amp;James L. Cox</p>
            <p>Philadelphia</p>
            <p>Jas. Madison  Secry of State</p>
            <p>Septr. 27, 1805  relative to</p>
            <p>Ship New Jersey</p>
            <pb n="2" facs="0012_002414_000286_0002.jpg" xml:id="d4e51"/>
            <p>Department of State</p>
            <p>Septr 27, 1805</p>
            <p>Gentlemen,</p>
            <p>I have received your memorial respecting the proceedings at Paris in the case of the ship New Jersey and cargo, in
				       which the Companies you represent are interested as insurers, and I have the honor to inform you, that on the
				       previous application of other parties ( Messrs. Nichlin &amp;Griffith ) the step has been taken which the circumstances
				       seemed to render proper.</p>
            <p>I have the honor to be</p>
            <p>Gentlemen</p>
            <p>Very respectfully 
				       your most Obt Servt.</p>
            <p>James Madison</p>
            <p>Charles Pettit and</p>
            <p>James L. Cox, Esquires</p>
            <p>Philadelphia</p>
         </div>
      </body>
